@startuml
title UC-09: Create In-Store Order - Process Flow
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E1F5FF
skinparam activityBorderColor #0277BD
skinparam activityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam activityDiamondBorderColor #F57F17
skinparam activityStartColor #4CAF50
skinparam activityEndColor #F44336

start
:Open create in-store order;
:Choose service type;

if (Service type?) then (Takeaway)
  :Skip table assignment;
else (Dine-in)
  :Select table from current layout;
  if (Table available for assignment?) then (No)
    :Show unavailable-table message;
    :Return to table selection;
    :Select table from current layout;
  else (Yes)
  endif
endif

:View menu;
:Select items, quantities,
toppings, and notes;
if (Selected item available?) then (No)
  :Show item-unavailable message;
  :Return to item selection;
  :Select items, quantities,
  toppings, and notes;
else (Yes)
  :Add selected items to order;
endif

if (Add more items?) then (Yes)
  :Continue selecting items;
else (No)
endif

:Review order details
and total amount;
:Confirm order;
note right
UC-09 covers in-store counter order creation
for Dine-in and Takeaway only.
Table assignment is applied only for Dine-in.
Takeaway payment continues in the payment flow.
Pickup orders belong to a separate process.
end note
if (Order contains at least one item?) then (No)
  :Show empty-order message
and continue adding items;
  :Return to item selection;
  :View menu;
  :Select items, quantities,
  toppings, and notes;
  :Review order details
  and total amount;
  :Confirm order;
else (Yes)
  if (Service type?) then (Dine-in)
    :Create dine-in order
and assign selected table;
    :Update table usage,
send kitchen ticket,
and show success message;
    stop
  else (Takeaway)
    :Create takeaway order with
pending online payment;
    :Continue to payment flow;
    stop
  endif
endif
@enduml
